One of the men who allegedly robbed an American couple touring in Addo last week has been arrested. The Port Elizabeth K9 unit arrested the man &#8211; one of five suspects &#8211; in the Coega area as he was trying to flee. Four other suspects managed to escape. Some of the stolen items were recovered. The couple &#8211; Robert Webb, 61, and Verna Yocum, 67, of Texas &#8211; were tied up after being robbed while taking photographs on the R334 last week. &nbsp; Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share